						               													<description>Volley back and forth with your opponent and score the most points to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Set &amp;amp; Attack was voted best 2 or more player game, most innovative mechanic, best rulebook, best card-only game, and took 3rd place overall in the 2022 1-Card PnP Design Contest on BoardGameGeek.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAMEPLAY&amp;#10;After an initial SERVE and RECEIVE, each turn you may SET (pass the ball within your court) or send the ball to the opponent&amp;rsquo;s court with an ATTACK or SPIKE (strong attack). But be careful &amp;ndash; SETS can be misplayed,and SPIKES can be BLOCKED!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For each action you will:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     draw an arrow or other symbol in an empty ball, and&amp;#10;     flip the card. (You may NOT look at the back of the card before flipping) The card is flipped vertically for a SET, RECEIVE or BLOCK, and horizontally for a SERVE, ATTACK, or SPIKE.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You score a point when:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     There are no empty balls in the path of your ATTACK, SPIKE or BLOCK. (Successful ATTACK, SPIKE, or BLOCK)&amp;#10;     There are no empty balls in the path of your opponent's RECEIVE, SET, or BLOCK. (Failed RECEIVE, SET, or BLOCK)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when there are no empty balls in the back court to serve from.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The BASIC GAME is played with just two actions: RECEIVE &amp;amp; ATTACK.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE ADVANCED GAME is played with all six actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
